5|$|In Gilmore's introduction, he lists {{a number}} of novels and films {{supposedly}} influenced by <b>The</b> <b>Satanic</b> Bible and LaVeyan Satanism. These include the novels Rosemary's Baby by Ira Levin and Our Lady of Darkness by Fritz Leiber, as well as films such as Rosemary's Baby, The Devil's Rain, The Car, and Dr. Dracula. Others have lauded <b>The</b> <b>Satanic</b> Bible as heavily influential on metal and rock bands such as Black Sabbath, Venom, King Diamond, and Marilyn Manson.|$|E
