500|$|<b>The</b> Nine <b>Satanic</b> Statements outline <b>the</b> basic {{ideology}} of LaVeyan Satanism, {{and have become}} some of the guiding principles of LaVeyan Satanism. They {{also served as a}} template for later publications by LaVey, such as his 1987 [...] "Nine Satanic Sins". Ayn Rand's influence on LaVeyan Satanism is apparent in <b>the</b> Nine <b>Satanic</b> Statements, leading some, namely Nikolas Schreck, to assert that the Statements are simply unacknowledged paraphrase of Rand's thoughts. These accusations have been disproved, however.|$|R
